<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">
<taxonomicName LSID="C885DF1B-28C3-56E9-A8C8-D8729381DF0A" authority="Rossman &amp; Dixon, 1975" authorityName="Rossman &amp; Dixon" authorityYear="1975" class="Reptilia" family="Dipsadidae" genus="Helicops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helicops yacu" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yacu">Helicops yacu Rossman &amp; Dixon, 1975</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossman &amp; Dixon" authorityYear="1975" class="Reptilia" family="Dipsadidae" genus="Helicops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helicops yacu" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yacu">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">Helicops yacu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all congeners by the combination of having an entire nasal scale and intergenials present (for information on references, see Suppl. material 3).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rossman &amp; Dixon" authorityYear="1975" class="Reptilia" family="Dipsadidae" genus="Helicops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Helicops yacu" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yacu">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">Helicops yacu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from north-eastern of the Province Loreto, Peru and one locality in north-western Acre, Brazil (
<bibRefCitation author="Rossman, Douglas Athon" journalOrPublisher="Herpetologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" pagination="412 - 414" refId="B6769925" refString="Rossman, Douglas Athon, Dixon, James Ray, 1975. A new colubrid snake of the genus Helicops from Peru. Herpetologica 31 (4): 412 - 414" title="A new colubrid snake of the genus Helicops from Peru" volume="31" year="1975">Rossman and Dixon 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira, Cristiano C." journalOrPublisher="South American Journal of Herpetology" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" refId="B7341469" refString="Nogueira, Cristiano C., Argolo, Antonio J. S., Arzamendia, Vanesa, Azevedo, Josue A., Barbo, Fausto E., Bernils, Renato S., Bolochio, Bruna E., Borges-Martins, Marcio, Brasil-Godinho, Marcela, Braz, Henrique, Buononato, Marcus A., Cisneros-Heredia, Diego F., Colli, Guarino R., Costa, Henrique C., Franco, Francisco L., Giraudo, Alejandro, Gonzalez, Rodrigo C., Guedes, Thais, Hoogmoed, Marinus S., Marques, Otavio A. V., Montingelli, Giovanna G., Passos, Paulo, Prudente, Ana L. C., Rivas, Gilson A., Sanchez, Paola M., Serrano, Filipe C., Silva, Nelson J., Struessmann, Christine, Vieira-Alencar, Joao Paulo S., Zaher, Hussam, Sawaya, Ricardo J., Martins, Marcio, 2019. Atlas of Brazilian Snakes: Verified Point-Locality Maps to Mitigate the Wallacean Shortfall in a Megadiverse Snake Fauna. South American Journal of Herpetology 14" title="Atlas of Brazilian Snakes: Verified Point-Locality Maps to Mitigate the Wallacean Shortfall in a Megadiverse Snake Fauna" volume="14" year="2019">Nogueira et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F6767210" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution of Helicops yacu. White circles represent literature reports. For the coordinates and references of the distribution points from literature, see Suppl. material 2." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e69234.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/614682" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" type="taxonomic remark">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">Taxonomic remark</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">
In 
<bibRefCitation author="Rossman, Douglas Athon" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Louisiana Academy of Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" refId="B6769943" refString="Rossman, Douglas Athon, Abe, Augusto Shinya, 1979. Comments on the taxonomic status of Helicops yacu (Serpentes: Colubridae). Proceedings of the Louisiana Academy of Sciences 42 (7-9)" title="Comments on the taxonomic status of Helicops yacu (Serpentes: Colubridae)" volume="42" year="1979">Rossman and Abe (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, the authors express their doubt that 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. yacu" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" rank="species" species="yacu">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">H. yacu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represents a valid species. They state the possibility that individuals assigned to 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. yacu" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" rank="species" species="yacu">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">H. yacu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might represent a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. pastazae" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234" rank="species" species="pastazae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="69234">H. pastazae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, they state that further specimens are needed for an accurate assessment. No further verification of this hypothesis has been made since then.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
